Juncker Says Europe, U.S., G-7 Ready for Further Action on Yen

-- B y   S t e p h a n i e   B o d o n i
-- 
2011-03-23T16:18:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/juncker-says-europe-u-s-g-7-ready-for-further-action-on-yen.html
Luxembourg Prime Minister Jean-
Claude Juncker said  Europe , the U.S. and the Group of Seven are
“ready” to take further action to curb the yen’s rise if
necessary.  “The G-7 countries and the three big central banks --
 Japan , the U.S. and Europe -- stand ready to further act against
this trend in a coordinated action,” Juncker told reporters in
Luxembourg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephanie Bodoni in Luxembourg at 
 sbodoni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net  